<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,311,1018,1044]" box="[189,311,1018,1044]" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,311,1018,1044]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="84" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,311,1018,1044]" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[187,1399,1065,1232]" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">
Generally dark brown. Metope and coryphe joined at nearly right angle (in lateral view). Metope without median carina but with weak sublateral carinae. Phallobase with median groove ventrally; each dorsolateral phallobase lobe with short horn-shaped process apically. Aedeagus with pair of long ventral hooks (
<superScript attach="none" box="[278,287,1170,1184]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">4</superScript>
/ 
<subScript attach="left" box="[295,304,1179,1193]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="84">5</subScript>
of aedeagus length) arising subapically. Style with deeply concave hind margin. Male anal tube equally wide (in dorsal view).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,702,1271,1344]" pageId="4" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
